From 8a1c3f2e5b7d9a0c4e6f8b2d1a3c5e7f9b0d2e4a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrew Sorensen <andrew@andrewsorensen.net>
Date: Sat, 1 Mar 2026 00:00:00 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] NAU8810: fix PLL mode BCLK divider calculation

The NAU8810 BCLK divider auto-configuration in pcm_hw_params assumes
IMCLK = 256*fs, which is correct for MCLK prescaler mode. However,
in PLL mode nau8810_calc_pll produces IMCLK = 1024*fs due to the 4x
PLL multiplication factor in the target formula. This causes BCLK to
run 4x too fast (e.g. 6.144 MHz instead of 1.536 MHz for 48 kHz
stereo 16-bit), producing audio static/noise as the DMA cannot supply
data at the accelerated frame rate.

Fix by increasing the BCLK divider by 4x (2 steps in the power-of-2
divider selection) when PLL mode is active.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Sorensen <andrew@andrewsorensen.net>
---
 sound/soc/codecs/nau8810.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/codecs/nau8810.c b/sound/soc/codecs/nau8810.c
index 2e8105b46..4f7a9c312 100644
--- a/sound/soc/codecs/nau8810.c
+++ b/sound/soc/codecs/nau8810.c
@@ -713,6 +713,9 @@ static int nau8810_pcm_hw_params(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream,
 			bclk_div = NAU8810_BCLKDIV_2;
 		else
 			return -EINVAL;
+		/* PLL mode IMCLK is 4x higher; increase BCLK divider to match */
+		if (nau8810->clk_id == NAU8810_SCLK_PLL)
+			bclk_div += (2 << NAU8810_BCLKSEL_SFT);
 		regmap_update_bits(nau8810->regmap, NAU8810_REG_CLOCK,
 			NAU8810_BCLKSEL_MASK, bclk_div);
 	}
